The paper proposes a new approach to improve the sample efficiency in goal-directed reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper introduces two new algorithms that modify state-of-the-art reinforcement learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.RO (Robotics), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
